Package perfcenter.baseclass

This package contains classes that define basic components of a distributed system.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Device
    This class defines devices that would be deployed on Host.
    DeviceServiceTime
    Defines service times.
    DistributedSystem
    This is the complete representation of the input file.
    Distribution
    This represents a distribution.
    Helper
    This class has static helper functions called by perfcenter.
    Host
    This represents the host definition in the input file.
    Lan
    Defines LAN.
    LanLink
    Used for defining connection parameters(mtu,prop,trans,headersize) between two lans
    Metric
    Holds value, confidence interval and confidence level of any performance or power metric.
    ModelParameters
    All model input parameters in one class.
    Node
    This is used to make tree for a scenario
    Queue
    Queue class is the primitive queue which resides in all the components of distributed system.
    QueuingResource
    This class abstracts the queuing resources like Device, LanLink and SoftServer.
    Scenario
    This class holds a Scenario, as defined in the input file.
    SoftServer
    Defines server .
    Task
    Defines the Task and operations done on task
    Variable
    Stores the variable that is defined in the input file
    VirtualResource
    Defines virtual resource.

Package perfcenter.baseclass Description

This package contains classes that define basic components of a distributed system. Its agnostic to the solution method.
